TekExpress may pause for user interaction (popup dialogs). During state polling, when TEKEXP:STATE? returns 'WAIT' or 'ERROR', check for popups: popup = tekexp.query('TEKEXP:POPUP?'). If popup exists, respond: tekexp.write('TEKEXP:POPUP "OK"'). Common popups: calibration reminders, test warnings, configuration confirmations. Without popup handling, TekExpress test will hang indefinitely in WAIT state. Always include popup handling in the polling loop. The Blockly tekexp_wait_state block automatically generates popup handling code.
# Inside state polling loop
state = tekexp.query('TEKEXP:STATE?').strip()

if state in ('WAIT', 'ERROR'):
    popup_msg = tekexp.query('TEKEXP:POPUP?').strip()
    if popup_msg:
        print(f'TekExpress popup: {popup_msg}')
        tekexp.write('TEKEXP:POPUP "OK"')
    else:
        print(f'TekExpress state: {state} (no popup)')

